WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

00:00:04.905 --> 00:00:11.706
He was a villain whose presence
sent shivers down one's spine.

00:00:11.786 --> 00:00:18.003
His name is Krishna Niranjan Singh,
well known as K. N. Singh.

00:00:19.488 --> 00:00:25.272
'I'd like to appreciate that
Indian women are braver than men.'

00:00:25.352 --> 00:00:29.812
He was born on September
1st 1908 in Dehradun.

00:00:29.892 --> 00:00:34.440
He was a villain of olden
times who gained lot of fame..

00:00:34.520 --> 00:00:36.710
..and gave a new style to this genre.

00:00:36.790 --> 00:00:38.926
I will never let you marry her.

00:00:39.196 --> 00:00:42.471
'But we love each other, dad.
We are in love.'

00:00:42.551 --> 00:00:46.766
K. N. Singh's father never wanted him
to join the film industry.

00:00:46.961 --> 00:00:52.182
His plan was to make
him a barrister like him.

00:00:52.262 --> 00:00:58.398
It was during British rule and
K. N. Singh went to London to study law.

00:01:00.702 --> 00:01:05.297
He finished his senior Cambridge
from Lucknow,

00:01:05.377 --> 00:01:08.356
Latin being his special subject.

00:01:08.436 --> 00:01:13.912
But once in a courtroom,
he saw a criminal was acquitted..

00:01:13.992 --> 00:01:15.394
..despite committing murder.

00:01:15.474 --> 00:01:18.571
And his own father
had saved the murderer.

00:01:18.651 --> 00:01:25.415
Seeing injustice overpower truth,
he gave up on practicing law.

00:01:26.551 --> 00:01:30.237
He was also an athlete and
was good at weight lifting.

00:01:30.317 --> 00:01:33.318
He was almost qualified
for Berlin Olympics.

00:01:33.398 --> 00:01:36.702
He wanted to join the Army too.

00:01:36.782 --> 00:01:40.864
But destiny had something else
in store for him.

00:01:40.944 --> 00:01:45.698
He had to go to Kolkata
where he met Prithviraj Kapoor..

00:01:45.778 --> 00:01:50.552
..who was a family friend
and also a prominent actor.

00:01:50.632 --> 00:01:56.271
He introduced K. N. Singh to
the famous director Debki Bose.

00:01:56.465 --> 00:02:02.173
Debki Bose offered K. N. Singh the role
of a doctor in 'Sunehra Sansar'.

00:02:02.253 --> 00:02:06.400
'You need one week's rest.'
'Complete bed rest!

00:02:06.779 --> 00:02:08.498
You are not supposed to even think.'

00:02:08.578 --> 00:02:13.125
This happened in 1936 and that's how
he started off his career.

00:02:13.205 --> 00:02:16.649
He worked in 4 more films
while he was in Kolkata.

00:02:16.729 --> 00:02:20.271
'Hawai Daku', 'Ananthashram',
'Vidyapati' and 'Mila'.

00:02:20.351 --> 00:02:21.385
'What hymns are those?'

00:02:21.465 --> 00:02:23.548
'These are love songs
of Radha and Krishna.'

00:02:23.628 --> 00:02:28.208
Film director A. R. Kardar
brought K. N. Singh to Mumbai.

00:02:28.288 --> 00:02:31.415
K. N. Singh gradually
became a famous villain.

00:02:32.010 --> 00:02:34.323
'Kamini!
- Let me go!'

00:02:34.403 --> 00:02:39.556
K. N. Singh never learnt acting,
but he put in lot of hard work..

00:02:39.636 --> 00:02:42.768
..to learn the character he played.

00:02:42.848 --> 00:02:46.444
He played a horse rider
in the film 'Inspector'.

00:02:46.524 --> 00:02:51.525
To play that character,
he spoke to many 'Victoria drivers'..

00:02:51.605 --> 00:02:56.562
..and observed their speech, lifestyle
and how they rode horse carts.

00:02:56.642 --> 00:02:58.915
'Are you Ganga?!'

00:02:59.714 --> 00:03:04.503
He was also seen in Raj Kapoor's
films like 'Barsat' and 'Awara'.

00:03:04.583 --> 00:03:06.719
'God definitely exists.
- Why?'

00:03:06.799 --> 00:03:09.270
'In the river,
I found my daughter-in-law.'

00:03:09.350 --> 00:03:11.887
The entire film industry
called Raj Kapoor as Raaj sahib..

00:03:11.967 --> 00:03:16.839
..while he called him Raj
because he knew Raj Kapoor..

00:03:16.919 --> 00:03:19.087
..since the time he was a child.

00:03:19.167 --> 00:03:24.297
Also note that film 'Awara'
was a hit in Russia..

00:03:24.377 --> 00:03:30.860
..and K. N. Singh was the only actor
who dubbed for himself in Russian.

00:03:30.940 --> 00:03:33.660
None of the other actors
could speak Russian.

00:03:33.740 --> 00:03:35.757
'A gentleman's child
is a good Samaritan..'

00:03:35.837 --> 00:03:38.049
'..while a dacoit's
child is always a dacoit.'

00:03:38.129 --> 00:03:40.470
K. N. Singh came a
long way in his career.

00:03:40.550 --> 00:03:43.865
He was famous for his sharp eyes,

00:03:43.945 --> 00:03:46.493
dressing style and significant voice.

00:03:46.573 --> 00:03:51.498
Gradually, his vision blurred 
but voice remained stern.

00:03:52.277 --> 00:03:56.407
He worked right from black and white
films to color films.

00:03:56.487 --> 00:03:59.629
He saw many actors
turning into a superstar.

00:03:59.709 --> 00:04:04.602
His journey came to an end
on 31st January, 2000.

00:04:04.682 --> 00:04:10.592
He lived in King Circle in Mumbai
and he breathed his last there.

00:04:10.672 --> 00:04:16.138
His name will be remembered with pride
in the history of Indian cinema.

